post_text:
Breckenridge Junior High School

502 West Lindsey

Breckenridge, TX 76424

Dear Parents,

We need your help! With the sudden closure of school this Spring, students were not able to return all of their school issued equipment, technology or Library books. We need all of those materials back so that we can take inventory and make plans for the 2020-2021 school year. All school issued property has replacement fees. The most common fees are as follows:

ALL Library books - $10

ALL calculators - $100

However, tomorrow, July 1st from 11am - 1 pm will be accepting ALL items with no penalty. This means that YOU WILL NOT BE CHARGED IF YOU RETURN ITEMS (INCLUDING LIBRARY BOOKS AND/OR CALCULATORS) TOMORROW. We will begin preparing invoices for missing materials Thursday, July 2, 2020.

There will be a return box located by the front doors of BJH and at the Buckaroo Field House. You may return items at either location tomorrow only.

Thanks!

BJH Administration

Laura Gibson, Principal

Monica Pearce, Asst. Principal

post_text:
Last weekend, five BJHS students traveled to Fort Worth for the Divisional Contest for Texas Alliance of Minorities in Engineering, or TAME. There were over 100 students from several large urban schools at the competition, and our Broncos came home with 3 1st place medals, a 3rd place medal, a 5th place ribbon, and 2 Judges' Choice Awards. Great job, Broncos!! #BroncoStrong

1st Place 7th Science - Josh
5th Place 7th Science - Jocelyn
3rd Place 8th Math - Lynzi
1st Place 7th Math - Antley
ACE Award for 7th (Top Math & Science Combined Score) - Antley (Qualifies for State TAME competition)
Judges' Award for Teamwork - Mixed team including Lynzi
Judges' Award for Perseverance - Mixed team including Jocelyn

Breckenridge High School
August 14, 2019 at 2:47 PM ·

In an attempt to be more transparent with fundraising that goes on at school, we have developed the attached form which MUST be completed by any group raising money on behalf of BISD Students, organizations, or campuses. Any group doing fundraising that takes place on campus or results in a donation of funds, supplies, or equipment to the school or student group must complete this form and have it on file with the campus principal before the fundraising begins.

If you are planning a fundraiser in which the proceeds will be used to assist our students in any way, please get this form filled out.

We have copies in the high school office.

Thank you!

shared_text:
Breckenridge ISD
December 6, 2018 at 5:31 PM ·

We have a higher than normal presence of law enforcement at the High School today. This morning we received a report of a threat, via some scribbling on a bathroom wall. Law enforcement were immediately called in and an investigation has been going on since then. At this time, there is no evidence that this threat is credible. Law Enforcement presence will remain high, and everyone will remain on a higher level of alert; however, we are carrying on with school activities. Please remember that at times like these, maintaining normality actually helps to identify when something is out of the ordinary. The threat was time specific and will expire tomorrow; however, law enforcement presence will be maintained. Thank you for your understanding as we take every precaution to keep our kids safe.

shared_text:
Breckenridge ISD
February 22, 2018 at 12:28 PM · Breckenridge, TX ·

THURSDAY WEATHER UPDATE

While we were optimistic temperatures would allow for some thawing this morning, it appears that will not happen in time for a 10am start.

BISD will remain closed, Thursday.

Administration will begin working on a plan to address missed time, as this closing will take us over the allowable limits. Thank you for your patience as we try to make the best decisions possible for our kids and community. That often means waiting until weather presents itself, rather than reacting to forecasts which are not always accurate.

Tim Seymore
Superintendent

post_text: If you are a parent of child participating in UIL, please take a moment to read this post from our UIL coordinator. Thanks so much!
shared_text:
Breckenridge Junior High is feeling excited.
November 28, 2017 at 8:02 PM ·

Please take time to read this message from our campus UIL Coordinator, Mr. Burchett

UIL Participants and Families,

First of all, thank you so much for signing up to do UIL and we wish you the best of luck as you take on the challenge of your event(s). UIL is on Tuesday, December 12th in Tolar, TX at their Junior High School. We will need to be pulling out of the parking lot here no later than 7:00 AM. We will have an early bus and a late bus bringing students back at different times later that afternoon. The last event is scheduled to begin at 3:00 PM. The school will be giving each participant $5 for their lunch. Any other purchases they must make with their own money. We know that you will represent the school and community to the best of your abilities. Thanks again, and GOOD LUCK Broncos!!!!!
